window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>NEW YORK TIMES</i></b><b> BESTSELLER </b>•<b> “[A] masterpiece . . . an astonishing book that will leave you questioning your own life and political views.”—</b><b><i>USA Today</i></b><br> <br> <b>“If any one person can be given credit for transforming the medical establishment’s thinking about health care for the destitute, it is Paul Farmer. . . . [</b><b><i>Mountains Beyond Mountains</i></b><b>] inspires, discomforts, and provokes.”—</b><b><i>The New York Times</i></b><b> (Best Books of the Year)</b> <br> <br> In medical school, Paul Farmer found his life’s calling: to cure infectious diseases and to bring the lifesaving tools of modern medicine to those who need them most. Tracy Kidder’s magnificent account shows how one person can make a difference in solving global health problems through a clear-eyed understanding of the interaction of politics, wealth, social systems, and disease. Profound and powerful, <i>Mountains Beyond Mountains</i> takes us from Harvard to Haiti, Peru, Cuba, and Russia as Farmer changes people’s minds through his dedication to the philosophy that “the only real nation is humanity.”<br> <br> <b>WINNER OF THE LETTRE ULYSSES AWARD FOR THE ART OF REPORTAGE</b></p>"; 
